  "body": "Add an unstable (for now) flag to rustc (--include-arguments-from FILE) which causes rustc to read additional arguments (\\0 separated) from the specified FILE or stdin if FILE is '-'.\n\nI consider this pull request still a work-in-progress, because it's currently lacking any kind of test, but I wanted to publish it now to get some feedback, mainly on whether the current approach is the correct one and if this kind of change would require an RFC.\n\nThe pull request was inspired by rust-lang/cargo#1241.\n",
